PrecisRe-appointment of RHODA RAND WITHERLY, of Prince Rupert, British Columbia, as chairman of the board of directors of the Prince Rupert Port Corporation to hold office during pleasure for a term effective March 23, 1999 and ending May 31, 1999; and approval of the appointment by the Minister of Transport of RHODA RAND WITHERLY, of Prince Rupert, British Columbia, as a part-time director of the Board of Directors of the Canada Ports Corporation to hold office during pleasure for a term ending May 31, 1999, in the place of Raymond Lemay, whose term has expired.
